<paragraph id="537D36A6FFFBFFE5E1FD00CDFDBCFE6E" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
It is noted that 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFBFFE5E04F00CDFD8DFF71" author="Korb, S. K." box="[373,558,151,178]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="61 - 62" refId="ref9613" refString="Korb, S. K. (1998) Some corrections on the diurnal butterflies (Lepidoptera: Rhopalocera) from Xinjiang Province, China. Entomotaxonomia, 20 (1), 61 - 62." type="journal article" year="1998">Korb (1998: 62)</bibRefCitation>
synonymised 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFFBFFE5E3E900CDFAADFF72" authority="Huang &amp; Murayama, 1992" authorityName="Huang &amp; Murayama" authorityYear="1992" box="[723,1294,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="scotosia" subSpecies="weiwueria">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E3E900CDFC70FF73" box="[723,979,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">M. scotosia weiwueria</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFBFFE5E2E600CDFAADFF72" author="Huang, R. - X. &amp; Murayama, S." box="[988,1294,151,177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 22" refId="ref9428" refString="Huang, R. - X. &amp; Murayama, S. (1992) Butterflies of Xinjiang Province, China. Tyo to Ga, 43 (1), 1 - 22." type="journal article" year="1992">Huang &amp; Murayama, 1992</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
[TL: 
<collectingCountry id="2BD57636FFFBFFE5E46800CDFA3BFF72" box="[1362,1432,151,177]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="9106F844FFFBFFE5E1AD00E1FF5FFF16" box="[151,252,187,213]" country="China" name="Xinjiang Uygur" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">Xinjiang</collectingRegion>
, Altai, Jiadengu], with nominate 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFFBFFE5E34E00E1FC29FF16" authority="Butler, 1878" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1878" box="[628,906,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scotosia">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E34E00E1FD55FF17" box="[628,758,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">M. scotosia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFBFFE5E3C400E1FC29FF16" author="Butler, A. G." box="[766,906,187,213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="281 - 286" refId="ref8862" refString="Butler, A. G. (1878) On some butterflies recently sent home from Japan by Mr. Montague Fenton. Cistula Entomologica, 2 (19), 281 - 286." type="journal article" year="1878">Butler, 1878</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFBFFE5E2F800E1FB2BFF15" author="Lang, S. - Y." box="[962,1160,187,214]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" refId="ref10103" refString="Lang, S. - Y. (2012) The Nymphalidae of China (Lepidoptera: Rhopalocera) Part 1: Lebytheinae, Calinaginae, Morphinae, Heliconiinae, Nymplalinae, Charaxinae, Apaturinae, Cyrestinae, Biblidinae, Limenitidae. Tshikolovets Publications Pardubice, Czech Republic, 443 pp." type="book" year="2012">Lang (2012: 160)</bibRefCitation>
synonymised it with 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFFBFFE5E44400E1FD80FF3A" authority="Higgins (1940: 53)" authorityName="Higgins" authorityPageNumber="53" authorityYear="1940" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="scotosia" subSpecies="butleri">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E44400E1FEE6FF3A" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">M. scotosia butleri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFBFFE5E0710085FD80FF3A" author="Higgins, L. G." box="[331,547,222,249]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="51 - 53" refId="ref9340" refString="Higgins, L. G. (1940) A new species and two new subspecies of Melitaea (Lep. Nymphalidae). Entomologist, 73, 51 - 53." type="journal article" year="1940">Higgins (1940: 53)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. From Huang &amp; Murayama’s monochrome figure of a worn specimen (1992: 8, fig. 17 no. 19), it is almost impossible to provide specific identification. However, 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFBFFE5E57C0159FA3FFEDE" author="Korb, S. K. &amp; Bolshakov, L. V." box="[1094,1436,259,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 123" refId="ref9703" refString="Korb, S. K. &amp; Bolshakov, L. V. (2011) A catalogue of butterflies (Lepidoptera: Papilioformes) of the former USSR. Second edition, reformatted and updated. Eversmannia Supplement 2, 1 - 123. [In Russian]" type="journal article" year="2011">Korb &amp; Bolshakov (2011: 42)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFBFFE5E1F2017DFDF4FE82" author="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G." box="[200,599,294,321]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" refId="ref11693" refString="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G. (2014) The genus Melitaea Fabricius, 1807 (Lepidoptera, Nymphalidae, Nymphalinae) Taxonomy and systematics with special reference to the male genitalia. Tshikolovets publications, Pardubice, Czech Republic, 360 pp." type="book" year="2014">van Oorschot &amp; Coutsis (2014: 65)</bibRefCitation>
placed this taxon in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFFBFFE5E2C1017DFBC5FE82" authorityName="Alpheraky" authorityYear="1881" box="[1019,1126,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibina">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E2C1017DFBC5FE82" box="[1019,1126,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">M. sibina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which seems to be a more plausible interpretation (although not indisputable, possibly requiring further investigation), since the distance to Altai in 
<collectingRegion id="9106F844FFFBFFE5E1C90135FE1DFE4A" box="[243,446,367,393]" country="China" name="Xinjiang Uygur" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">Xinjiang province</collectingRegion>
is more than 
<quantity id="943A9B43FFFBFFE5E36C0135FD1FFE4A" box="[598,700,367,393]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" unit="km" value="1000.0">1000 km</quantity>
. northwest of the widely recognized distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFFBFFE5E5C40135FA23FE4B" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1878" box="[1278,1408,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scotosia">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFBFFE5E5C40135FA23FE4B" box="[1278,1408,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">M. scotosia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in northeast 
<collectingCountry id="2BD57636FFFBFFE5E03F01C9FEE8FE6E" box="[261,331,403,429]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="2BD57636FFFBFFE5E06C01C9FE3EFE6E" box="[342,413,403,429]" name="South Korea" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">Korea</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="2BD57636FFFBFFE5E0E201C9FDB8FE6E" box="[472,539,403,429]" name="Japan" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">Japan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
